\sum^n_{r=1} (2r+1)f(r) =xf(r) -y
(n+1)^2 - n^2 = 2n+1
\sum_{r=1}^n (2r+1)f(r)
n^2 f(n)
(n+1)^2 f(n) - n(n+1)/2
\textbf{Proof}
n=1
4 - 1 = 3 = (2+1)f(1)
(n+1)^2 f(n) - n(n+1)/2
(n+2)^2 f(n+1) - (n+1)(n+2)/2 - [(n+1)^2 f(n) - n(n+1)/2]  = (n+2)^2 f(n+1) - (n+1)^2 (f(n+1)-1/(n+1)) - (n+1)  = (2n+3)f(n+1) = (2(n+1)+1)f(n+1)
